                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11279: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-05T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 5, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 5—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“November 5, 1 p.m. A widespread distribution of troops recently arrived
                            from Honan to areas overrun with bandits and Communists indicates that
                            at least a serious effort is being made to curb activities of these
                            elements. Troops in large numbers have been despatched provinces
                            Kiangsi, Northwest and North Hunan and West and North Hupeh. Military
                            authorities here state that Loshan, Honan, has been retaken by
                            Government forces but no word has been received <pb facs="0309" n="211"
                                xml:id="pg_211"/> concerning Reverend Nelson. There is an
                            unconfirmed rumor in Sinyangchow that Nelson has died of disease. Am
                            seeking further light on report. Repeated to Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
